Enums/TraceType.html#/s:13SwiftValhalla9.name: through
Enums/TraceType.html#/s:13SwiftValhalla9.abstract: A through location is a location at which we neither allow u-turns nor generate legs or arrival/departure maneuvers.

Enums/Driveability.html#/s:13SwiftValhal.abstract: Travel is allowed only in the backward direction.

Enums/DirectionType.html#/s:13SwiftValha.name: instructions
Enums/DirectionType.html#/s:13SwiftValha.abstract: Indicating that maneuvers with instructions should be returned (this is the default if not specified).

Enums/CostingModel.html#/s:13SwiftValhal.name: auto
Enums/CostingModel.html#/s:13SwiftValhal.abstract: Standard costing for driving routes by car, motorcycle, truck, and so on that obeys automobile driving rules, such as access and turn restrictions. Auto provides a short time path (though not guaranteed to be shortest time) and uses intersection costing to minimize turns and maneuvers or road name changes. Routes also tend to favor highways and higher classification roads, such as motorways and trunks.

Enums/CostingModel.html#/s:13SwiftValhal.name: bicycle
Enums/CostingModel.html#/s:13SwiftValhal.abstract: Standard costing for travel by bicycle, with a slight preference for using cycleways or roads with bicycle lanes. Bicycle routes follow regular roads when needed, but avoid roads without bicycle access.

Enums/CostingModel.html#/s:13SwiftValhal.name: pedestrian
Enums/CostingModel.html#/s:13SwiftValhal.abstract: Standard walking route that excludes roads without pedestrian access. In general, pedestrian routes are shortest distance with the following exceptions: walkways and footpaths are slightly favored, while steps or stairs and alleys are slightly avoided.

Enums/CostingModel.html#/s:13SwiftValhal.name: bus
Enums/CostingModel.html#/s:13SwiftValhal.abstract: Standard costing for bus routes. Bus costing inherits the auto costing behaviors, but checks for bus access on the roads.

Enums/CostingModel.html#/s:13SwiftValhal.name: bikeshare
Enums/CostingModel.html#/s:13SwiftValhal.abstract: A combination of pedestrian and bicycle. Use bike share station(amenity:bicycle_rental) to change the travel mode

Enums/CostingModel.html#/s:13SwiftValhal.name: truck
Enums/CostingModel.html#/s:13SwiftValhal.abstract: Standard costing for trucks. Truck costing inherits the auto costing behaviors, but checks for truck access, width and height restrictions, and weight limits on the roads.

Enums/CostingModel.html#/s:13SwiftValhal.name: taxi
Enums/CostingModel.html#/s:13SwiftValhal.abstract: Standard costing for taxi routes. Taxi costing inherits the auto costing behaviors, but checks for taxi lane access on the roads and favors those roads.

Enums/CostingModel.html#/s:13SwiftValhal.name: motorScooter
Enums/CostingModel.html#/s:13SwiftValhal.abstract: Standard costing for travel by motor scooter or moped. By default, motor_scooter costing will avoid higher class roads unless the country overrides allows motor scooters on these roads. Motor scooter routes follow regular roads when needed, but avoid roads without motor_scooter, moped, or mofa access.

Enums/CostingModel.html#/s:13SwiftValhal.name: motorcycle
Enums/CostingModel.html#/s:13SwiftValhal.abstract: Standard costing for travel by motorcycle. This costing model provides options to tune the route to take roadways (road touring) vs. tracks and trails (adventure motorcycling).

Enums/CostingModel.html#/s:13SwiftValhal.name: multiModal
Enums/CostingModel.html#/s:13SwiftValhal.abstract: Currently supports pedestrian and transit. In the future, multimodal will support a combination of all of the above.

Enums/Language.html.name: Language
